2022-01-19 17:37:00	darkbasic92	Hello all. Is there any chance windows raid0 with dynamic disks would be more unstable by default? I launched a game that worked fine on a single faster drive and it crashed for the first time in history with no apparent reason. I am eager to blame the disk setup it could of course not be the case. I am now checking the disks all over again for bad sectors after like an hour of use
2022-01-19 17:37:10	-->	kts [kts] (Kyaw Thu Soe) (~kts@103.73.237.13) has joined #hardware
2022-01-19 17:38:09	SineDeviance	darkbasic92: did you use storage spaces? or the UI built into disk management to setup your raid0?
2022-01-19 17:38:17	darkbasic92	disk management
2022-01-19 17:38:30	SineDeviance	are you on Windows 10 Pro?
2022-01-19 17:38:31	-->	herman (Herman) (~herman@2603:9000:8500:baa0:603e:bdc3:4ff2:200) has joined #hardware
2022-01-19 17:38:33	darkbasic92	Yep
2022-01-19 17:39:05	SineDeviance	Okay, try using the Storage Spaces applet in control panel to set it up instead
2022-01-19 17:39:05	darkbasic92	Storage spaces better than dynamic disk stripe?
2022-01-19 17:39:26	darkbasic92	Will do, just have to copy everything back then
2022-01-19 17:40:00	SineDeviance	Technically the disk management utilities shouldn't cause instability with any config you setup, but Storage Spaces is a newer design. It's not technically software RAID but it's extremely similar
2022-01-19 17:41:26	SineDeviance	also, Storage Spaces supports formatting your pool with the REFS filesystem. 
2022-01-19 17:42:00	SineDeviance	NTFS will work fine, but you may see better performance with ReFS
2022-01-19 17:42:21	SineDeviance	ReFS is also better from a data-integrity standpoint
2022-01-19 17:42:51	SineDeviance	the performance benefits will be more obvious on SSD storage, but it should be a little snappier than NTFS on mechanical drives as well
2022-01-19 17:42:59	NiLon	single crash however isn't that telling, it could be anything. Even a bit flip from cosmic ray (and yes, that is a real problem)
2022-01-19 17:43:04	SineDeviance	yeah
2022-01-19 17:43:20	SineDeviance	could totally be a bug in the game that has just not been triggered yet
2022-01-19 17:43:46	SineDeviance	you can actually look at the crash log for that game in Event Viewer, it may give you some insight into why it crashed
2022-01-19 17:43:59	SineDeviance	if the game has it's own error logs you could check those too
