2022-01-19 18:04:39	SineDeviance	yes, ReFS is built into Windows 10 pro. ReFS cannot be used as a boot drive, it is designed to be used for mass storage
2022-01-19 18:04:59	darkbasic92	I see
2022-01-19 18:05:31	SineDeviance	Well, actually, you might be able to boot from ReFS the filesystem. But it's not designed for that, and your array won't be bootable because it doesn't exist until Windows is already booted
2022-01-19 18:05:42	SineDeviance	This is one of the drawbacks of software RAID setups
2022-01-19 18:06:06	darkbasic92	I see
