2022-01-20 00:37:49	SineDeviance	cheapie: that is due to poor line quality
2022-01-20 00:38:05	SineDeviance	the line cannot correctly carry the higher frequencies needed for 56k baud rate
2022-01-20 00:38:07	cheapie	SineDeviance: 33.6k is the maximum speed for V.34bis with good line quality.
2022-01-20 00:38:19	<--	itsalexjones (~itsalexjo@82.4.99.241) has quit (Read error: Connection reset by peer)
2022-01-20 00:38:23	SineDeviance	cheapie: I'm talking about V.92 on poor quality lines
2022-01-20 00:38:37	SineDeviance	often they will negotiate at lower rates to compensate and make the connection
2022-01-20 00:38:40	cheapie	V.92 can fall back to lower speeds, yes. That is a separate issue from this hard limit.
2022-01-20 00:39:07	cheapie	(V.34bis, V.34, and I think V.32 have this feature as well)
2022-01-20 00:39:47	SineDeviance	I see now where you said you were using V.34 above, whoops
2022-01-20 00:40:17	SineDeviance	is there a reason you went with that modem over a newer V.92 modem?
